dataValue.message:
Hi Mike Smith,

Thanks for sending that report last week. I read it yesterday, and I feel that Chapter 2 needs more specific information about our sales figures. I also felt that the tone could be more formal.

Engineers and scientists use e-mails to make requests, to answer questions, and to give announcements. E-mails are read quickly. For that reason, get to the point in the first paragraph--the first sentence, if possible. In other words, state what you want up front. Be careful about e-mails that make complaints, which are usually better handled in person.

In e-mails, keep the sentence lengths and paragraph lengths relatively short. Sentences should average fewer than twenty words, and paragraphs should average fewer than seven lines. In the format suggested here, you should single space your e-mails, skip a line between paragraphs, and use a typeface that is easily read on a computer. If possible, keep the total e-mail length to a length that can be viewed entirely on the screen.

Because the reader sees only the title of your e-mail in the Inbox or in the folder where it has been filed, give some thought to that title. Choose a title that orients the reader to the subject of the e-mail and, if possible, distinguishes your e-mail from other e-mails about that subject. For example, choose 'oposal Draft for Our ME 440W Design Project' as opposed to 'Design Project' or 'ME 440W.' With e-mails, send copies to anyone whose name you mention in the e-mail or who would be directly affected by the e-mail. Also, be sure to mention explicitly any attachments. Finally, remember that final paragraphs of e-mails generally tell readers what you want them to do or what you will do for them.

Also, I wanted to let you know that I've scheduled a meeting with the PR department for this Friday regarding the new ad campaign. It's at 11:00 a.m. and will be in the small conference room.

Please let me know if you can make that time.

Thanks!

Best regards,

dataSet.label: Form Widgets
dataSet.description: Individual form controls like input, text, textarea, calendar, date and time pickers and so on, automatically receive some global styling.

dataSet.label: Form
dataSet.description: Form widget provides a columnar group of input elements for user entry. Form can be bound to a web service via Service Variable and used to pass parameters needed to trigger the web service.

dataSet.label: Button and Anchor
dataSet.description: Use custom button and anchor styles for actions in forms, dialogs, and more. Includes support for a handful of contextual variations, sizes, states, and more.

dataSet.label: Data Table
dataSet.description: Data Table provides a tabular view for database Entities or API response data and can be bound to data sources like database tables, queries etc, or JSON objects through Live, Service or Static Variables, respectively.

dataSet.label: Cards
dataSet.description: Cards is a view of items that are rendered responsively across a wide range of mobile devices and screen sizes.

dataSet.label: List
dataSet.description: List widget provides a list view of items from a data source. List data can be obtained from various data sources like database, queries or web services through Live or Service variables defined at the time of data binding.

dataSet.label: Live filter
dataSet.description: Live Filter provides data filtering UI and functionality. It can be bound to a data source from database through the Live Variable. It returns filtered results which in turn can be bound to any widget.

dataSet.label: Charts
dataSet.description: “A picture is worth a thousand words”. To this end, WaveMaker gives you a tool to present your data in a pictorial form using the chart widgets.

dataSet.label: Iframe
dataSet.description: An inline frame (Iframe) is used to embed another document within the current HTML document. Frames allow a visual HTML Browser window to be split into segments, each of which can show a different document.

dataSet.label: Panel
dataSet.description: Panel can be used to group a set of widgets together. It has a collapsible title bar and you can add multiple panels, any number of multiple panes can be open at any given point of time.

dataSet.label: Tile
dataSet.description: Tile is a container for other widgets used to present a set of objects. Tile widget lets user to directly add an image, text box, video, or web code to user dashboard.

dataSet.label: Accordion
dataSet.description: An accordion is a stacked list of UI components, with only one focused component expanded at any point of time and the rest collapsed.

dataSet.label: Tabs
dataSet.description: Tabs can be used when you need multiple containers within a single window. The user can quickly access the content by switching between the panes without leaving the page.

dataSet.label: Dialogs
dataSet.description: WaveMaker provides the facility to add pop-up windows to your project through the Dialog widgets. This can be for alerts, getting additional information like user name, or for login purposes.

dataSet.label: Wizard
dataSet.description: Wizards UI are best suited for tasks that have multiple independent steps where in the user is taken through each step making it easier for the user to comprehend the task to be achieved in a structured manner.

dataSet.label: Media
dataSet.description: WaveMaker supports all three types of media – image, audio and video in the form of three widgets like Picture, Audio and Video.

dataSet.label: Navigation
dataSet.description: Navigation elements like Dropdown menu, Navbar, Breadcrumb provides navigation capabilities to help you in navigating from on page or view to another.

dataSet.label: Messages
dataSet.description: Message widget helps to display custom message on the page. Based on the message type – error, warning, success, info, loading– the message look and feel changes.

dataSet.label: Progress Bar and Spinner
dataSet.description: Progress Bar can be used to show the status of any given event. Progress may be either indeterminate or a numeric value between 0 and a given maximum.

dataSet.label: Notifications
dataSet.description: Notifications can be used to show the user a message or an alert based upon a user action. You can choose to show an alert, a confirm dialog or a toast notification.

dataSet.label: Carousel
dataSet.description: Carousel widget is a flexible, responsive way to add a slider to your site. The content is flexible enough to allow images, iframes, videos, or just about any type of content that you might want.
